## 5. Audit Mechanisms | –ú–µ—Ö–∞–Ω—ñ–∑–º–∏ –∞—É–¥–∏—Ç—É

### 5.1 Access Levels

| Level | Who | What They See |
|-------|-----|---------------|
| **Level 0 (Public)** | Anyone | Metadata via ZK-proof ("decision complied with W_life ‚Üí ‚àû") |
| **Level 1 (Restricted)** | Regulators, courts | Full log by legal request |
| **Level 2 (Internal)** | System owner | Full access, but access itself is logged |

### 5.2 Audit Workflow (Step-by-Step)

```
1. AUDIT REQUEST
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Auditor submits crypto-signed request
   
2. INTEGRITY VERIFICATION
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Check Merkle root hash
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ If mismatch ‚Üí FLAG TAMPERING (automatic, no debate)
   
3. COMPLIANCE ANALYSIS
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Compare log against AI-HPP rules
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Automated checks using standardized templates
   
4. REPORT GENERATION
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Auto-generated with ZK-proof
   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ If violation ‚Üí ESCALATE to regulator
```

### 5.3 Transparency Principles

**No double interpretation:**
- Access criteria are **unambiguous**
- Audit steps are **algorithmic** (not subjective)
- Violations are **automatically flagged**

